TitMainTitle: Group portrait of two women and three men, including man seated in center holding book with title "How to Write Better Letters" posed in domestic interior with birdcage, floral wallpaper, and plaque on wall that reads "All to myself I think of you - think of the things we used to do. Think of the things we used to say. Think of each happy yesterday. Sometimes I sigh and sometimes I smile. ... I keep each olden golden while. All to myself."
